Vice President Mike Pence participated in a "fireside chat" at Cornerstone Ministries Church in Pennsylvania. He discussed various topics, including his involvement in the pro-life movement, the importance of reelecting pro-life conservatives, and the contrast between the two tickets in the upcoming election. Pence also encouraged canvassers working to reach voters and asked for prayers for his family. He emphasized the need to continue working for the sanctity of life and promised to keep the promises made by the Trump administration.